goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?
goals.rationale: This will help identify airports with the highest number of bird strikes and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes at those airports.

goals.question: What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This will help identify the most vulnerable aircrafts and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes on those aircrafts.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by the amount of damage caused?
goals.rationale: This will help understand the severity of bird strikes and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes that cause substantial damage.

goals.question: What is the trend of bird strikes over time?
goals.rationale: This will help identify if there is an increasing or decreasing trend of bird strikes over time and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airline operator?
goals.rationale: This will help identify airlines with the highest number of bird strikes and inform decisions on measures to reduce bird strikes on those airlines.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    airport_counts = data['Airport_Name'].value_counts()
    ax = airport_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('Flight_Date').size().reset_index(name='count')
    
    plt.plot(data['Flight_Date'], data['count'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the trend of bird strikes over time?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
